Time Limit: 1 sec
Memory: 256 MB

Description

Given an integer N and an array A of N distinct numbers. Your task is to find the minimum and maximum numbers among them, swap these two numbers, and then print the array after the swap.

Input Format

The first line contains T, the number of test cases.

For each test case:
- The first line contains an integer N, the number of elements in the array.
- The second line contains N space-separated integers denoting the elements of the array.

It's guaranteed that all numbers are distinct.

Output Format

Print the array after the replacement operation.

Constraints

1 ≤ T ≤ 10
2 ≤ N ≤ 1000
-10^5 ≤ A[i] ≤ 10^5

Sample Input 1

1
5
4 1 3 10 8

Sample Output 1

4 10 3 1 8

Note

First, find the minimum and maximum numbers in the array [4, 1, 3, 10, 8], which are 1 and 10 respectively. By swapping these two numbers, the array becomes [4, 10, 3, 1, 8].
```

#include <iostream>
#include <vector>
using namespace std;

int main() {
    int t;
    cin>>t;
    while(t--)
    {
        int n;
        cin>>n;
        vector<int>v(n);
        for(int i = 0; i < n; i++)
        {
            cin>>v[i];
        }
       int maxele = 0;
        int minele = 0;
        for(int i = 0; i < n; i++)
        {
            if(v[i] > v[maxele])
            {
                maxele = i;
            }
            if(v[i] < v[minele])
            {
                minele = i;
            }
        }
        swap(v[maxele],v[minele]);

        for(int i = 0; i < n; i++)
        {
            cout<<v[i]<<" ";
        }
    }
    return 0;
}
